WEBVTT

00:01.459 --> 00:02.877
{\an5}WOW!

00:01.459 --> 00:02.877
Girl: ♪ I GOT THE BEAT ♪

00:02.961 --> 00:05.255
♪ SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE
WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:05.338 --> 00:08.425
♪ PICK IT UP, TURN AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:08.508 --> 00:11.261
[♪...]

00:12.679 --> 00:14.180
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, HEY) ♪

00:14.264 --> 00:16.433
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, LA) ♪

00:16.516 --> 00:17.726
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:17.809 --> 00:21.312
♪ I GOT THE BEAT SO ALL THE KIDS
DANCE WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:21.396 --> 00:25.400
♪ STICK 'EM UP, ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:25.483 --> 00:29.028
[♪...]

00:29.112 --> 00:30.530
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:30.613 --> 00:33.158
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B. ♪

00:33.241 --> 00:35.577
[MUSIC ENDS]

00:36.703 --> 00:40.123
{\an8}Captioning Provided By:
MTV NETWORKS

00:40.206 --> 00:42.125
[♪...]

00:46.421 --> 00:49.507
Bessie: WHEE!

00:49.591 --> 00:51.968
AGAIN, AGAIN,
FASTER, FASTER, AGAIN!

00:52.051 --> 00:55.013
LAST ONE TO THE TOP
SMELLS LIKE HAPPY.

00:55.096 --> 00:56.264
[HAPPY GROWLS]

00:56.931 --> 00:58.641
[CHUCKLES]: COME ON, HAPS.

00:58.725 --> 00:59.809
BACK IT UP THIS TIME.

00:59.893 --> 01:02.312
RUNNIN' START,
RUNNIN' START... READY?

01:02.395 --> 01:04.813
ROLL!

01:06.274 --> 01:06.983
OH!

01:07.066 --> 01:08.193
[GRUNTS]

01:08.276 --> 01:10.111
HAPPY... HAPPY,
I CAN'T STOP.

01:13.865 --> 01:14.616
Bessie: OH!

01:14.699 --> 01:16.993
OH... WHOA, WHOA.

01:18.077 --> 01:19.162
{\an1}WHOA!

01:18.077 --> 01:19.162
[BARKS]

01:19.245 --> 01:21.581
[WIND HOWLS]

01:23.541 --> 01:24.709
[JET-LIKE ZOOM]

01:27.670 --> 01:29.506
[SIGHS]: SWEET,
HUH, HAPS?

01:29.589 --> 01:31.216
[GROANING]

01:31.299 --> 01:32.675
[BONES CRUNCHING]

01:32.759 --> 01:34.886
OOH, OW, AH.

01:34.969 --> 01:37.222
OH, HAPPY...

01:37.305 --> 01:38.932
{\an1}MAN, LOOK AT US,
WE'RE ALL BANGED UP.

01:39.015 --> 01:40.558
WHAT A PAIR, HUH?

01:40.642 --> 01:42.477
[WHINING]

01:42.560 --> 01:43.311
[PANTING]

01:43.394 --> 01:47.106
[SILENT]

01:47.190 --> 01:48.358
AW, WOULD A BISCUIT
MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER BOY?

01:48.441 --> 01:50.568
[SOBBING]

01:50.652 --> 01:52.362
AH!

01:52.445 --> 01:53.863
[SLURP... CHOMPING]

01:53.947 --> 01:55.698
WELL... [SIGHS]

01:55.782 --> 01:56.991
WE BETTER GET US
TO THE DOCTOR.

02:03.873 --> 02:04.707
HAPPY, DON'T BE
SUCH A FRAIDY-CAT.

02:04.791 --> 02:06.167
GOING TO THE DOCTOR
IS NO BIG DEAL.

02:08.627 --> 02:10.588
[GROANING...]

02:15.844 --> 02:17.428
[HAPPY YELPS]

02:17.512 --> 02:19.681
{\an4}COME ON, HAPPY,
DON'T BE
SUCH A BABY.

02:17.512 --> 02:19.681
[GROANING]

02:19.764 --> 02:21.933
I YANK BECAUSE I LOVE.

02:22.016 --> 02:23.893
[PROTESTING BARK]

02:23.977 --> 02:25.520
NOW THAT'S JUST RIDICULOUS.

02:25.603 --> 02:29.232
HE DOES <i> NOT</i> PERFORM ALL KINDS
OF UNNECESSARY PROCEDURES

02:29.315 --> 02:31.401
{\an1}JUST TO RUN UP
YOUR BILL, HAPPY.

02:31.484 --> 02:33.319
THE VET IS YOUR FRIEND.

02:35.321 --> 02:36.906
[MAILMAN WHISTLES]

02:36.990 --> 02:38.741
[GRUNTS... MOANS]

02:38.825 --> 02:41.077
[SCREAMS]

02:41.161 --> 02:43.204
[GROANING...]

02:46.916 --> 02:50.211
{\an5}YOU'LL SEE.

02:46.916 --> 02:50.211
[HAPPY WHINES]

02:50.295 --> 02:52.213
HE'S GONNA FIX YOU RIGHT UP.

02:52.297 --> 02:53.965
MAYBE HE'LL EVEN
THROW IN A FLEA DIP.

02:55.758 --> 02:57.969
HIGGENBOTTOM, HAPPY W.?

02:58.052 --> 03:01.347
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

03:01.431 --> 03:01.848
[HAPPY YELPS]

03:01.931 --> 03:04.100
COME ON, HAPPY.

03:04.183 --> 03:05.101
HOW 'BOUT
A LITTLE COURAGE?

03:05.184 --> 03:08.104
{\an3}Receptionist: SMITH
"COMMA" SNOWBALL?

03:10.607 --> 03:11.608
[BELL TINKLES]

03:11.691 --> 03:13.693
AND A LITTLE SELF-RESPECT.

03:13.776 --> 03:14.903
[GROWLS]

03:16.529 --> 03:17.989
HA... HAPPY.

03:18.072 --> 03:19.991
GREAT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

03:20.074 --> 03:22.285
{\an3}WHAT BRINGS YOU
HERE TODAY, LITTLE FELLA?

03:22.368 --> 03:24.120
[GROWLS/SPITS]

03:24.203 --> 03:26.456
{\an5}HI, DOCTOR,
I'M BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
AND I CAN ANSWER THAT.

03:26.539 --> 03:28.958
HAPPY AND I ENGAGED IN
SOME OVERLY AGGRESSIVE PLAY

03:29.042 --> 03:32.921
{\an5}AND AS A RESULT,
SUSTAINED SOME MINOR
LACERATIONS AND CONTUSIONS.

03:33.004 --> 03:35.381
{\an3}[LAUGHS]: OOH-LA-LA,
FANCY MEDICAL TERMS, HUH?

03:35.465 --> 03:38.635
{\an3}WELL, LET'S JUST GET HIM UP
ON THE OLD EXAM TABLE

03:38.718 --> 03:39.636
AND TAKE A LOOK, SHALL WE?

03:39.719 --> 03:41.137
{\an1}[GROWLING]

03:41.220 --> 03:43.848
[GROWLING AND BARKING]

03:43.932 --> 03:46.392
OH, HAPPY, A VET
<i>IS</i> A REAL DOCTOR.

03:46.476 --> 03:47.226
JUST LOOK AT HIS DIPLOMAS.

03:50.897 --> 03:53.232
I AM SO SORRY, DOCTOR.

03:53.316 --> 03:55.652
HE'S USUALLY
BEAUTIFULLY BEHAVED.

03:55.735 --> 03:57.278
JUST GET UP HERE, MISTER.

03:57.362 --> 03:59.364
[WHINES]:
OH, AH [GROWLS]

03:59.447 --> 04:02.200
{\an4}THE TABLE'S
NOT FREEZING COLD,
IT'S ROOM TEMPERATURE.

04:02.283 --> 04:03.451
[WHINES]

04:03.534 --> 04:05.745
SUCH AN EXAGGERATOR.

04:05.828 --> 04:07.413
HE'S VERY CREATIVE.

04:07.497 --> 04:10.500
SO "HOPPY", LET'S SEE
WHAT'S WHAT HERE, HUH?

04:10.583 --> 04:12.126
RELAX, HAPPY.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.795
THIS WON'T HURT A BIT.

04:18.257 --> 04:19.257
[GRUNTS]: HUH?

04:19.341 --> 04:21.719
UH, DOCTOR,
IT'S ACTUALLY HIS KNEE

04:21.803 --> 04:23.680
OH...

04:23.763 --> 04:25.223
[CHUCKLES]:
YES, OF COURSE.

04:27.266 --> 04:28.768
[YELPS]

04:28.851 --> 04:31.688
LET'S GET THIS
ALL FIXED UP... NURSE!

04:39.821 --> 04:42.323
NOW THIS MAY STING
<i>JUST</i> A LITTLE BIT.

04:42.407 --> 04:44.158
[SIZZLES]

04:44.242 --> 04:45.618
[MOANING]

04:45.702 --> 04:46.828
OH, WITH THE DRAMA.

04:46.911 --> 04:48.955
HAPPY WALTER HIGGENBOTTOM...

04:49.038 --> 04:51.290
COME DOWN FROM YOUR
ORBIT THIS INSTANT.

04:51.374 --> 04:54.335
{\an3}WELL, WE CAN'T
HAVE THAT, CAN WE?

04:54.419 --> 04:54.460
{\an3}NURSE!

05:03.344 --> 05:04.679
RAWHIDE, HAPPY?

05:05.722 --> 05:06.973
[GROWLS]

05:09.642 --> 05:11.310
[DOOR SLAMS]

05:11.394 --> 05:14.272
{\an1}HE... HE MISSED
HIS NAP SO... [CHUCKLES]

05:19.318 --> 05:22.989
{\an3}AW, HAPPY, WHO LOOKS
CUTE IN A CONE?

05:23.072 --> 05:23.489
{\an3}YOU DO.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.578
[COMPLAINING WHINE]

05:28.661 --> 05:30.663
OH, LIGHTEN UP, SHEESH.

05:30.747 --> 05:32.915
OK, MY TURN.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.585
WATCH AND LEARN.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.587
MS. BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM.

05:37.670 --> 05:40.381
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT
TO SEE THE PHYSICIAN.

05:40.465 --> 05:41.340
HEY...

05:41.424 --> 05:42.175
YOUR DOCTOR IS OUT TODAY.

05:42.258 --> 05:44.635
YOU'LL BE SEEING
ANOTHER DOCTOR.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.679
UM... OK.

05:46.763 --> 05:48.139
ABIGAIL?

05:48.222 --> 05:49.891
...THE DOCTOR WILL SEE YOU NOW.

05:49.974 --> 05:53.770
GOOD LUCK
IN THERE, KID.

05:53.853 --> 05:57.065
LET'S SEE, UH-HUH,
OH, PERFECT TIMING.

05:57.148 --> 05:59.067
YOU'RE JUST IN TIME
FOR YOUR...

05:59.150 --> 06:00.943
[DEEP-VOICED]:
BOOSTER SHOT.

06:01.027 --> 06:03.905
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

06:03.988 --> 06:06.824
[GULPS] I'M SORRY, UM...

06:06.908 --> 06:09.952
{\an3}I REALIZE YOU'RE JUST
A RECEPTIONIST BUT, UM...

06:10.036 --> 06:12.038
I THOUGHT I MADE IT
CLEAR ON THE PHONE.

06:12.121 --> 06:15.041
I'M JUST HERE FOR
MY SPORTS INJURY TODAY.

06:15.124 --> 06:16.793
YOU KNOW, I REALLY
DON'T HAVE TIME TO GET

06:16.876 --> 06:18.503
[WHISPERS]: A SHOT.

06:18.586 --> 06:20.296
IT'LL ONLY TAKE A SECOND DEAR.

06:22.131 --> 06:24.425
JUST THE SAME,
MY DAY'S PRETTY PACKED

06:24.509 --> 06:28.638
{\an5}SO LET'S SAVE IT-
MAYBE RESCHEDULE IT
FOR ANOTHER TIME, "K"?

06:28.721 --> 06:30.640
{\an3}OH, SHALL WE CALL
YOUR MOTHER?

06:30.723 --> 06:32.809
NO, THAT WON'T
BE NECESSARY.

06:34.685 --> 06:35.937
UGH... AHH!

06:36.020 --> 06:37.230
OH!

06:37.313 --> 06:40.108
[BARKING LAUGH]

06:40.191 --> 06:41.484
KNOCK IF OFF, HAPPY.

06:41.567 --> 06:43.027
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

06:43.111 --> 06:46.072
{\an4}YOUR STUPID CONE
DOESN'T EVEN BEGIN TO
COMPARE TO A BOOSTER SHOT.

06:46.155 --> 06:47.657
BOOSTER SHOT, OHH...

06:47.740 --> 06:50.201
IN AND OUT.

06:50.284 --> 06:51.077
[GASPING]

06:51.160 --> 06:54.330
IN AND OUT, IN AND OUT...

06:54.413 --> 06:58.835
[CLOCK TICKING...]

06:58.835 --> 07:00.837
OH, AH!

07:00.920 --> 07:02.338
[LAUGHING]

07:02.421 --> 07:04.757
[MENACING LAUGH]

07:04.841 --> 07:06.092
[LAUGH CONTINUES]

07:06.175 --> 07:06.968
OH, OH.

07:07.051 --> 07:09.762
OK, RELAX, RELAX.

07:09.846 --> 07:11.097
NO PROBLEM, NO PROBLEM.

07:11.180 --> 07:11.973
[DOOR OPENS]

07:15.601 --> 07:19.939
[BOY WHIMPERS]

07:20.022 --> 07:20.773
WHAT THE?

07:20.857 --> 07:22.525
{\an5}[BOY CRYING]

07:20.857 --> 07:22.525
YOU HEAR THAT HAPPY?

07:22.608 --> 07:23.442
[BOY CRYING]

07:23.526 --> 07:25.111
HOW COME THEY'RE
TAKING ANOTHER ONE IN?

07:25.194 --> 07:27.363
WHAT ABOUT ABIGAIL?

07:27.446 --> 07:28.322
WHERE'D SHE GO,
WHERE'S ABIGAIL?

07:28.406 --> 07:30.449
WHY HASN'T SHE COME OUT YET?

07:30.533 --> 07:32.201
[MOANS]

07:32.285 --> 07:35.329
I MEAN... ONE OUT, ONE IN,
AM I RIGHT?

07:35.413 --> 07:36.664
AM I RIGHT,
AM I RIGHT, HAPPY?

07:36.747 --> 07:37.039
[DOOR OPENS]

07:37.123 --> 07:38.875
BESSIE...

07:38.958 --> 07:42.128
[SINISTER]: HIGGENBOTTOM?

07:53.389 --> 07:57.185
Doctor: OK, CHUCKY, OPEN WIDE.

07:58.561 --> 08:00.521
[CHUCKY GAGGING]

08:04.150 --> 08:06.068
{\an1}HOP UP, DEAR,
HOP UP.

08:06.152 --> 08:08.237
{\an1}THE DOCTOR WILL
BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

08:11.657 --> 08:13.659
[CREAKING AND GROANING]

08:17.872 --> 08:19.582
BESSIE.

08:23.085 --> 08:25.171
[DOOR OPENS]

08:26.547 --> 08:27.882
[DARTH VADER-LIKE BREATHING]

08:27.965 --> 08:30.051
BE...SSIE.

08:30.134 --> 08:31.928
WHAT BRINGS YOU HERE TODAY,
LITTLE FELLA?

08:32.010 --> 08:33.179
ER, UH, GAL?

08:33.261 --> 08:36.265
OH, JUST YOUR RUN-OF-THE-MILL,
SPORTS RELATED FLESH WOUND.

08:36.349 --> 08:37.058
NO BIGGIE.

08:37.140 --> 08:39.769
UH... NO BIGGIE, INDEED.

08:39.852 --> 08:43.105
{\an1}NOTHING A LITTLE TIME AND SOME
HEALTHY BACTERIA CAN'T FIX.

08:43.188 --> 08:46.943
YOU MEAN, I CAN... GO?

08:47.026 --> 08:49.612
{\an1}SURE, GREAT
SEEING YOU, "BOSSIE."

08:49.695 --> 08:51.864
{\an4}YOU CAN PAY
THE RECEPTIONIST
ON THE WAY OUT.

08:51.948 --> 08:53.157
[GROWLS]

08:53.241 --> 08:57.620
OH, WAIT A SECOND.

08:57.703 --> 08:59.830
WHAT HAVE WE HERE?

08:59.914 --> 09:02.208
[PANTING]

09:02.291 --> 09:05.002
YOU'RE GETTING A BOOSTER SHOT.

09:05.086 --> 09:06.379
{\an3}NURSE!

09:06.462 --> 09:08.047
NOW, NOW, NOW...

09:08.130 --> 09:10.466
LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA, LET'S...

09:10.549 --> 09:11.759
LET'S BE REASONABLE ABOUT THIS.

09:11.842 --> 09:14.220
THIS CAN WAIT ANOTHER
SIX MONTHS, RIGHT?

09:14.303 --> 09:15.513
OH, I AM AFRAID NOT DEAR.

09:15.596 --> 09:18.808
BUT DON'T WORRY,
IT'LL ONLY HURT... A LOT.

09:18.891 --> 09:20.309
[LAUGHING]

09:20.393 --> 09:22.144
[SCREAMS]

09:20.393 --> 09:22.144
[YELPS]

09:22.228 --> 09:23.521
HAPPY, COME ON.

09:23.604 --> 09:24.355
HUH?

09:33.197 --> 09:34.448
[GASPS]

09:35.908 --> 09:36.826
[BOTH SCREAM]

09:39.537 --> 09:40.705
OOH!

09:40.788 --> 09:41.872
[POWER SAW BUZZES]

09:41.956 --> 09:42.790
[SCREAMING]

09:43.916 --> 09:44.709
AH.

09:46.919 --> 09:48.629
{\an3}[GASPING]

09:48.713 --> 09:49.588
[SCREAMING]

09:50.923 --> 09:51.882
AHH.

09:53.175 --> 09:55.303
OH, SORRY, DOCTOR.

09:55.386 --> 09:56.554
Happy: [INDISTINCTLY]
"THEY WENT THAT WAY."

10:09.608 --> 10:11.193
{\an5}[X-RAY STATIC BUZZ]

10:09.608 --> 10:11.193
Nurse: UH-HUH.

10:11.277 --> 10:12.862
{\an3}[GASPS] MY BASKET
WEAVING BADGE.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.071
HAPPY, I'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOR THAT.

10:14.155 --> 10:15.823
AFTER THEM, DOCTOR.

10:15.906 --> 10:16.741
[SCREAMS]

10:20.286 --> 10:21.746
HUH!

10:21.829 --> 10:22.621
[GROANS]

10:25.750 --> 10:29.086
[MUZAK PLAYS]

10:29.170 --> 10:30.004
[CHATTERING]

10:45.269 --> 10:48.147
[GASPING/PANTING]

10:49.815 --> 10:51.317
NO!

10:49.815 --> 10:51.317
[YELPS]

11:01.994 --> 11:03.120
BINGO.

11:03.204 --> 11:06.207
Bessie: OW!

11:06.290 --> 11:07.583
...OW!

11:07.666 --> 11:09.210
[HOWLING...]

11:09.293 --> 11:11.253
{\an5}[BESSIE YELLS]

11:09.293 --> 11:11.253
[HAPPY HOWLS]

11:13.339 --> 11:16.092
[SIGHS] SEE, HAPPY?

11:16.175 --> 11:17.718
THAT WASN'T SO...

11:17.802 --> 11:18.260
{\an5}[THROBBING LOUDLY]

11:17.802 --> 11:18.260
OK, YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:18.344 --> 11:21.263
UH, THAT HURTS.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.265
YUP, THAT'S GONNA SMART
FOR A FEW DAYS.

11:27.645 --> 11:29.188
[SLURPS] OW.

11:29.271 --> 11:31.774
[SLURPS... GRUNTS]

11:31.857 --> 11:34.610
[LAUGHTER]

11:36.028 --> 11:38.781
[♪...]

11:46.539 --> 11:48.916
{\an5}Mary Francis Gibbons: AND THE
WINNER OF THE "WHAT IT MEANS
TO BE A BEE" VIDEO CONTEST

11:48.999 --> 11:52.837
{\an3}WILL ATTEND A PRIVATE TEA
WITH MIRIAM BREEDLOVE

11:52.920 --> 11:55.381
THE PRESIDENT OF
THE NATIONAL HONEYBEES.

11:55.464 --> 11:58.300
YOU'LL BE ALLOWED TO ASK
THREE QUESTIONS OF YOUR CHOICE.

11:58.384 --> 11:58.926
{\an5}[GASPING]

11:58.384 --> 11:58.926
Girl: WHOA, ARE YOU SERIOUS?

11:59.009 --> 12:00.177
Girl 2: MIRIAM BREEDLOVE?

12:00.261 --> 12:01.470
WOW!

12:01.554 --> 12:02.680
CAN I GET A WHAT-WHAT?

12:03.931 --> 12:05.224
WOW-WOW-WOW.

12:05.307 --> 12:06.434
{\an3}WISHING ON
A STAR WORKS.

12:06.517 --> 12:08.811
AWESOME-AWESOME-AWESOME-AWESOME.

12:08.894 --> 12:11.147
THE WINNER...

12:11.230 --> 12:12.982
WILL BE ANNOUNCED
LATER THIS WEEK.

12:13.065 --> 12:16.026
NOW GIRLS, LET'S GET BACK TO
OUR ARTS AND CRAFTS PROJECT.

12:18.028 --> 12:20.823
Being a, um, Honeybee

12:20.906 --> 12:24.869
means that I have someplace
to go on Saturdays

12:24.952 --> 12:28.789
when my Grandma has
her knitting circle over?

12:28.873 --> 12:30.124
[Snoring]

12:30.207 --> 12:32.710
And, uh...

12:32.793 --> 12:33.752
[White noise]

12:35.671 --> 12:38.007
What's up Honeybee wannabees?

12:38.090 --> 12:39.467
Welcome to my ultra-glam life.

12:39.550 --> 12:41.844
If you wanna know me-

12:41.927 --> 12:43.721
you gotta start with the closet.

12:55.399 --> 12:58.861
Oh, hello,
I didn't see you there.

12:58.944 --> 13:02.448
{\an5}I'm Bessie Higgenbottom,
and I'd like to share with you
what it means to be a Bee.

13:02.740 --> 13:04.575
{\an3}BEN?

13:04.658 --> 13:07.995
HONEYBEES ARE THE OLYMPIANS
OF GIRLS AGES SEVEN TO 12.

13:08.078 --> 13:10.956
TROOP 828 KEEPS ME IN
TOP PHYSICAL CONDITION.

13:11.040 --> 13:12.124
[GROANS]: AHH...

13:16.128 --> 13:18.255
[♪...]

13:20.966 --> 13:23.511
[GRUNTING]

13:25.846 --> 13:28.432
[GRUNTS] NOT IMPRESSED?

13:28.516 --> 13:30.559
WHAT IF I TOLD YOU
I JUST DID ALL THAT

13:30.643 --> 13:31.977
WHILE BALANCING
A LADYBUG ON MY NOSE?

13:34.897 --> 13:37.733
A HONEYBEE ISN'T ALL
JUST PHYSICAL PROWESS.

13:37.816 --> 13:39.401
AH!

13:39.485 --> 13:42.238
SHE MAINTAINS
HER MENTAL FITNESS AS WELL.

13:43.113 --> 13:44.615
{\an1}[CRASH]

13:44.698 --> 13:47.243
THE THIRD POINT OF THE
HONEYBEE TRIANGLE IS HEART.

13:49.620 --> 13:50.871
{\an3}WATCH THIS.

13:51.622 --> 13:55.334
FEAR NOT, OLD PERSON.

13:55.417 --> 13:58.629
{\an6}A HONEYBEE IS HERE
TO HELP YOU SAFELY
CROSS THE ROAD.

13:58.712 --> 13:59.964
OOH, UH.

14:00.798 --> 14:03.175
A HONEYBEE'S JOB
IS ITS OWN REWARD.

14:03.259 --> 14:04.009
OOH.

14:06.554 --> 14:09.098
OH, MY, HELLO AGAIN.

14:09.181 --> 14:12.518
YOU JUST CAUGHT ME READING
ONE OF MY FAVORITE CLASSICS:

14:12.601 --> 14:14.562
"THE HONEYBEE HANDBOOK."

14:14.645 --> 14:17.314
PEOPLE OFTEN ASK ME,
"BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM...

14:17.398 --> 14:18.440
[CRASH]

14:18.524 --> 14:22.653
WHAT HAPPENED TO PAGES 123
TO 126 OF THE HANDBOOK?"

14:22.736 --> 14:25.322
GREAT QUESTION, PEOPLE,
AND WELL OBSERVED.

14:25.406 --> 14:27.449
BECAUSE THEY'RE MISSING.

14:27.533 --> 14:28.492
WHY?

14:28.576 --> 14:29.785
ANOTHER GREAT QUESTION.

14:29.868 --> 14:32.705
SOME SAY IT'S BECAUSE
THEY REVEAL TOO MUCH!

14:32.788 --> 14:35.541
OH, I'M SORRY,
I GOT EXCITED.

14:35.624 --> 14:37.167
OK, OK.

14:37.251 --> 14:41.297
SOME SAY THEY REVEAL TOO MUCH,
SUCH AS A SMALL FACT

14:41.380 --> 14:44.758
THAT WHOEVER EARNS
EVERY HONEYBEE BADGE

14:44.842 --> 14:48.053
WILL BECOME A SUPERHERO
CALLED "THE MIGHTY B!"

14:48.137 --> 14:48.679
[FAST REWIND]

14:48.762 --> 14:50.681
"The Mighty B!"

14:50.764 --> 14:52.558
"The Mighty B!"

14:52.641 --> 14:54.518
"The Mighty B..."

14:54.602 --> 14:56.937
{\an5}AND THE WINNER OF
THE HONEYBEE VIDEO CONTEST IS:

14:54.602 --> 14:56.937
[ALL GASPING]

14:57.021 --> 14:58.105
[CRUNCHING]

14:58.606 --> 15:00.649
[EXCITED GROAN]

15:03.819 --> 15:05.279
[STRAINED GROAN]

15:05.362 --> 15:07.906
[SURPRISED GRUNT]

15:07.990 --> 15:10.117
[MONOTONE]: BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM.

15:10.200 --> 15:11.368
[GASPS]

15:14.622 --> 15:18.959
I WON!

15:22.755 --> 15:24.632
Bessie: TEA WITH MIRIAM
AT LE FANCY.

15:26.675 --> 15:28.469
OK, PLACES EVERYONE.

15:28.552 --> 15:30.346
WE ONLY HAVE SIX MORE
DAYS OF REHEARSAL

15:30.429 --> 15:32.765
UNTIL "OPERATION
DREAM COME TRUE."

15:32.848 --> 15:36.852
{\an1}SIX MORE DAYS UNTIL TEA
WITH MIRIAM BREEDLOVE, OH.

15:36.935 --> 15:38.354
WHERE IS THE STUNT TEA?

15:38.437 --> 15:39.897
BRING ME THE STUNT TEA.

15:39.980 --> 15:42.274
[CHINA RATTLING]

15:43.901 --> 15:45.778
[SIGHS]

15:45.861 --> 15:48.030
MISS MANNERS SAYS

15:48.113 --> 15:51.742
{\an6}TO PICK UP THE
SAUCER AND TEACUP
IN ONE SWIFT MOTION

15:51.825 --> 15:55.329
{\an3}TAKING CARE TO MAINTAIN
RAISED PINKIES.

15:56.789 --> 15:59.541
[INHALES] BENJAMIN?

16:01.543 --> 16:05.464
{\an5}[SIGHS] I'D BETTER GET
TO BE YOUR SIDEKICK WHEN
YOU BECOME THE MIGHTY B.

16:05.547 --> 16:06.840
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

16:06.924 --> 16:08.676
CONGRATS,
STINKENBOTTOM.

16:08.759 --> 16:09.551
AIR FIVE.

16:12.179 --> 16:14.473
UM, PLEASE TELL ME THIS IS
NOT HOW YOU PLAN TO DO TEA

16:14.556 --> 16:16.100
WITH MIRIAM BREEDLOVE?

16:19.478 --> 16:21.105
WHAT, THAT'S NOT RIGHT,
NO PINKIES UP?

16:23.315 --> 16:25.734
{\an1}POOR MESSY,
YOU NEED OUR HELP.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.569
AGAIN, REPEAT AFTER ME.

16:27.653 --> 16:29.738
OH, CRUMPETS...

16:29.822 --> 16:32.116
DON'T MIND IF I DO.

16:32.199 --> 16:35.077
{\an5}[ENGLISH ACCENT]:
OH, CRUMPETS,
DON'T MIND IF I DO.

16:35.160 --> 16:37.621
{\an3}NOW, MESSY, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
DO WHEN THE CRUMPETS ARE SERVED?

16:37.705 --> 16:39.456
{\an1}GRAB THEM OFF THE PLATE,
DUNK 'EM IN THE TEA

16:39.540 --> 16:40.582
AND STUFF 'EM IN MY FACE.

16:43.544 --> 16:45.212
{\an1}ACCENT!

16:45.838 --> 16:48.090
{\an5}[ENGLISH ACCENT]:
GRAB THEM OFF THE PLATE,
DUNK THEM IN MY TEA

16:48.173 --> 16:50.384
AND STUFF THEM IN MY FACE.

16:50.467 --> 16:51.468
[GULP]

16:51.552 --> 16:54.388
ARE YOU GUYS SURE I HAVE
TO HAVE AN ENGLISH ACCENT?

16:54.471 --> 16:57.433
{\an6}OF COURSE YOU
HAVE TO HAVE
AN ENGLISH ACCENT, MESSY.

16:57.516 --> 16:59.101
{\an1}DUH, IT'S AN
ENGLISH HIGH TEA.

16:59.184 --> 17:01.979
{\an1}YOU'RE NOT GONNA
WEAR THAT, ARE YOU?

17:02.062 --> 17:03.939
UH, WELL, I, I...

17:04.021 --> 17:07.859
UM, BESSIE, MIRIAM WILL
"TOTES" DIG THIS OUTFIT.

17:07.943 --> 17:08.277
REALLY?

17:08.359 --> 17:10.820
{\an1}TRUST US.

17:19.704 --> 17:20.622
DONE.

17:20.705 --> 17:23.250
AN ENTIRE CONVERSATION
WITH NO QUESTIONS.

17:23.333 --> 17:25.169
I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED, FINGER.

17:25.252 --> 17:28.964
{\an5}BUT NOW I WON'T RISK
ACCIDENTALLY USING UP
ONE OF MY THREE QUESTIONS.

17:29.048 --> 17:31.550
PLANNING IS IMPORTANT WHEN
YOU'RE TALKING TO CELEBRITIES.

17:31.633 --> 17:32.801
[BUZZING ALARM]

17:32.885 --> 17:33.635
AH, WE GOTTA GO!

17:33.719 --> 17:37.473
[PHONE RINGING]

17:37.556 --> 17:39.141
YOU GOT HIGGENBOTTOM,
WHAT YOU GONNA DO?

17:39.224 --> 17:43.103
[SWEETLY]: HELLO,
MIRIAM BREEDLOVE'S ASSISTANT.

17:43.187 --> 17:43.645
UH-HUH, WHAT'S THAT?

17:43.729 --> 17:45.689
CHANGE OF LOCATION?

17:45.773 --> 17:48.442
UH-HUH, UH-HUH, OK, UH-HUH.

17:48.525 --> 17:51.028
[PANTING] I'D MEET HER
ON THE MOON IF I HAD TO.

17:51.111 --> 17:52.654
[CHUCKLES] I MEAN,
I'M REALLY EXITED [CHUCKLES].

17:52.738 --> 17:53.947
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
YOU CAUGHT ME.

17:54.031 --> 17:56.074
I WAS JUST ABOUT TO LEAVE SO...

17:56.158 --> 17:57.326
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

17:57.409 --> 17:58.368
NOT SOON ENOUGH.

17:58.452 --> 17:59.828
{\an4}I'M REALLY,
REALLY EXCITED...
OK, BYE.

17:59.912 --> 18:02.706
[BOTH LAUGHING]

18:05.918 --> 18:09.171
MIRIAM WANTS TO MEET
AT THE TOP OF A SKYSCRAPER?

18:09.254 --> 18:10.547
WELL, I GUESS IT IS A HIGH TEA.

18:10.631 --> 18:13.550
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

18:15.010 --> 18:17.304
[FOOTSTEPS ECHO]

18:20.015 --> 18:21.350
[ENGLISH ACCENT]: PARDON ME.

18:21.433 --> 18:22.142
BREEDLOVE, PARTY OF TWO?

18:23.602 --> 18:25.854
NO?

18:26.980 --> 18:29.191
THIS MUST BE
A ONE, NOT A SEVEN.

18:29.274 --> 18:31.693
[SHEEP BLEATING]

18:31.777 --> 18:34.696
THIS DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

18:34.780 --> 18:36.573
MAYBE IT WAS A LEFT.

18:39.326 --> 18:41.203
COME ON, LEGS, GO FASTER.

18:41.286 --> 18:44.122
[SHEEP BLEATING]

18:44.206 --> 18:46.125
WE CAN'T KEEP MIRIAM WAITING.

18:49.127 --> 18:50.379
[SHEEP BLEAT]

18:50.462 --> 18:53.382
Bessie: RESERVATIONS FOR
BREEDLOVE, MIRIAM BREEDLOVE?

18:53.465 --> 18:55.717
YES,<i> THE</i> MIRIAM BREEDLOVE?

18:55.801 --> 18:59.513
HELLO, CONCIERGE?

18:59.596 --> 19:01.014
SOME ASSISTANCE, PLEASE?

19:03.183 --> 19:07.187
[SHEEP BLEATING...]

19:07.271 --> 19:08.063
[GASPS]

19:10.649 --> 19:12.818
[SHEEP BLEATING...]

19:12.901 --> 19:16.071
{\an5}[STRING QUARTET PLAYS]

19:12.901 --> 19:16.071
[BLEATING CONTINUES]

19:19.157 --> 19:19.575
[ALL BLEAT]

19:19.157 --> 19:19.575
WAIT OUTSIDE.

19:19.658 --> 19:21.910
Sheep: BAH?

19:21.994 --> 19:22.786
I DON'T KNOW,
COUNT EACH OTHER.

19:22.870 --> 19:25.581
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM?

19:25.664 --> 19:26.832
YOU'RE 23 MINUTES LATE.

19:26.915 --> 19:28.750
{\an1}23 MINUTES AND
49 SECONDS LATE.

19:28.834 --> 19:32.170
OH, I WISH IT WAS 23 MINUTES.

19:32.254 --> 19:34.089
I CANNOT DESCRIBE
THE HUMILIATION I FEEL.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.173
I'M SO SORRY.

19:36.258 --> 19:37.384
WELL...

19:37.467 --> 19:38.927
NOW YOU ONLY HAVE SIX MINUTES
WITH MISS BREEDLOVE.

19:39.011 --> 19:41.597
SIX MINUTES,
SIX MINUTES?

19:41.680 --> 19:43.348
I, UH, I, I...

19:43.432 --> 19:46.059
UH, I-I-I-I-I'D
GET TO IT.

19:46.143 --> 19:48.145
[DISTANT SHEEP BLEATING]

19:48.228 --> 19:49.688
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
YOU'RE ON.

19:49.771 --> 19:51.773
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

19:51.857 --> 19:54.276
COOL LIKE A CUCUMBER.

19:54.359 --> 19:56.987
COOL LIKE A CUCUMBER,
COOL LIKE A CUCUMBER.

20:09.917 --> 20:15.130
[GASPING]

20:15.213 --> 20:18.842
WELL, I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO GIVE UP ON YOU.

20:18.926 --> 20:20.802
GLAD YOU MADE IT.

20:20.886 --> 20:24.181
Bessie: OH, UH, UH...

20:25.307 --> 20:28.727
[ENGLISH ACCENT]:
HELLO BESSIE, I'M MIRIAM.

20:28.810 --> 20:30.646
[LAUGHS] <i> I'M</i> MIRIAM,
<i>YOU'RE</i> BESSIE.

20:30.729 --> 20:34.858
OH, RIGHT, RIGHT.

20:34.942 --> 20:36.944
NO, BESSIE IS ME-
I'M BESSIE AND YOU'RE MIRIAM.

20:37.027 --> 20:38.779
[CHUCKLES]: I MEAN, THAT'S...
YOU AREN'T ME.

20:38.862 --> 20:41.198
[FLUSTERED]: I'M JUST...

20:41.281 --> 20:42.115
THAT'S CRAZY,
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

20:42.199 --> 20:44.534
YOU'RE MIRIAM,
AND I'M BESSIE, UH...

20:44.618 --> 20:47.329
[SIGHS] HIGGENBOTTOM
IS MY LAST NAME AND...

20:47.412 --> 20:48.455
I'M SO NERVOUS.

20:48.538 --> 20:50.332
{\an1}IT MUST BE HOT
UNDER THAT BONNET.

20:50.415 --> 20:52.334
YOU WANNA TAKE
THAT THING OFF?

20:52.417 --> 20:54.711
{\an6}WELL, SURE, IF...
IF YOU DON'T THINK IT'S
IMPROPER OF ME, THAT IS.

20:54.795 --> 20:56.546
[BATS SQUEALING]

20:56.630 --> 20:58.006
[GASPING]

20:59.675 --> 21:00.926
OF COURSE NOT.

21:01.009 --> 21:02.260
HOW 'BOUT SOME CAKE?

21:02.344 --> 21:03.345
{\an1}CAKE ALWAYS
CALMS MY NERVES.

21:07.933 --> 21:08.850
[MOANS]: UHH...

21:08.934 --> 21:12.646
{\an1}HONEY, I SAY IF IT
PICKS UP FOOD, THEN USE IT.

21:12.729 --> 21:15.107
BUT DOESN'T MISS MANNERS SAY
THAT THE PROPER DESSERT FORK

21:15.190 --> 21:17.067
{\an3}SHOULD POSSESS
EXACTLY THREE TINES?

21:17.150 --> 21:20.237
{\an3}[GASPS]: WAIT, WAIT, I DIDN'T
MEAN TO ASK YOU A QUESTION.

21:20.320 --> 21:21.029
I MEAN, I DID, BUT...

21:21.113 --> 21:22.698
BUT THAT WASN'T
ONE OF THEM.

21:22.781 --> 21:25.033
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

21:25.117 --> 21:26.576
DID I JUST WASTE ONE
OF MY THREE QUESTIONS, OH!

21:26.660 --> 21:28.870
{\an5}OH, WAIT, NO,
I DID IT AGAIN,
I'M SORRY.

21:28.954 --> 21:30.205
NO, UH...

21:30.288 --> 21:32.040
{\an3}DOES THAT COUNT
AS MY SECOND QUESTION?

21:32.124 --> 21:33.875
OH, I KEEP
ASKING QUESTIONS.

21:33.959 --> 21:36.211
HOW 'BOUT...
I BEND THE RULES?

21:36.294 --> 21:38.755
{\an1}WHY DON'T YOU ASK ME
WHATEVER YOU LIKE?

21:38.839 --> 21:41.258
AND IF I DON'T
WANNA ANSWER, I WON'T.

21:43.468 --> 21:45.220
WELL, UM...

21:45.303 --> 21:47.639
{\an5}I COULD ASK YOU ABOUT
WHY YOU CHOSE TO NARROW
THE WIDTH OF THE SASH

21:47.723 --> 21:49.349
BY AN EIGHTH OF
AN INCH FOR SPRING?

21:49.433 --> 21:50.767
{\an3}GREAT CALL,
BY THE WAY.

21:50.851 --> 21:53.562
OR, UM, WHY YOU DEDICATED
YOUR LIFE TO THE HONEYBEES?

21:53.645 --> 21:56.565
BUT... I REALLY JUST
WANNA KNOW ONE THING.

21:56.648 --> 21:58.317
GO AHEAD, FRED.

21:58.400 --> 22:01.153
I NEED TO KNOW THE TRUTH
ABOUT "THE MIGHTY B".

22:01.236 --> 22:04.072
YOU DO, DO YOU?

22:04.156 --> 22:07.242
WELL... I CAN
TELL YOU THIS.

22:07.325 --> 22:08.577
[SHEEP BLEATING]

22:12.247 --> 22:15.375
[SHEEP BLEATING...
PLATES CRASHING]

22:15.459 --> 22:17.544
[ELEPHANT TRUMPETS]

22:17.627 --> 22:19.421
{\an1}BUT YOU DIDN'T
HEAR THAT FROM ME.

22:19.504 --> 22:20.756
BUT I, UH...

22:20.839 --> 22:22.090
{\an5}MISS BREEDLOVE,
WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO MOVE

22:22.174 --> 22:23.550
{\an1}IF YOU'RE GOING TO
MAKE YOUR NEXT MEETING?

22:23.633 --> 22:25.761
SORRY, HON,
I GOTTA RUN.

22:27.471 --> 22:29.890
I KNEW IT!

22:30.265 --> 22:34.019
[♪...]

23:10.764 --> 23:12.724
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

23:12.808 --> 23:15.018
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
